 {"id":"bd-ieb0","title":"Unit Tests: Color Blending Edge Cases","description":"# Color Blending Edge Case Tests

## Current State
- src/color.rs has 8 tests - decent but missing edge cases
- Porter-Duff blending is core algorithm

## What Needs Testing

### Blend Edge Cases
- blend_over with src alpha = 0.0 (fully transparent)
- blend_over with src alpha = 1.0 (fully opaque)
- blend_over with dst alpha = 0.0
- blend_over with dst alpha = 1.0
- Both alphas near ALPHA_EPSILON
- Result alpha near zero handling

### Precision Tests
- Very small alpha values (1e-6)
- Many sequential blends (accuracy drift)
- Known precision limits documented

### Color Space Conversion
- to_256_color() full range testing
- to_16_color() all 16 mappings
- from_hsv() full hue range (0-360)
- from_hex() invalid formats
- Luminance calculation accuracy

### Bitwise Operations
- bits_eq() for identical colors
- bits_eq() for different colors
- to_bits() determinism

### Component Clamping
